org.wonderly.jini2
Class ConfigurableJiniApplication

java.lang.Object
  org.wonderly.jini2.NameableObjectImpl
      org.wonderly.jini2.ConfigurableJiniApplication
All Implemented Interfaces:
NameableObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
FindBrowser, JiniBrowse, JiniConfigEditor, JiniDeskTop, PersistentJiniService, ServiceSelector
public class ConfigurableJiniApplication
extends NameableObjectImpl

This class provides the basic infrastructure for using a Configuration object in an application. A Configuration object is constructed using ConfigurationProvider, in this classes constructor. The methods provided here have information in their documentation pertaining to which Configuration entries they read from to get the values that they return.

Configuration Values Recognized

Value NameTypeUsage
exporterExporterExporter for all proxies
loggingConfigStringThe contents of a logging.properties file that will be loaded to initialize logging configuration instead of setting -Djava.util.logging.config.file
logLevelLevelDefault log level for all loggers referenced
loggerLoggerLogger to use instead of the classname
entriesEntry[]The set of Entry objects that will initially be used at registration. If there is a serialized store already in place, that will always be used instead. That file can be removed to reset the Entry[] set to that specified here.
wireProtocolStringJRMP or JERI are recognized and default setup for SSL Jeri endpoints with no authentication is used if JERI is specified.
templateServiceTemplateUsed to do any lookups for services. locatorsLookupLocator[]Locators for service lookup etc.
lookupenvsLookupEnv[]The unicast locators to use for registration
groupsString[]The groups to use for registration
proxyTrustVerifierProxyTrustVerifierUsed to verify proxy of LUS to perform notification with.
preparerPreparerUsed to prepare the proxy of the LUS for registration.
otherLoggersString[]The names of other logging instances that should be manipulated by the setLogLevel() method to keep all of the associated loggers operating at the same log level. This makes in unnecessary to specify or manipulate a logging configuration file too.

Author:
Gregg Wonderly - gregg.wonderly@pobox.com

getExporter

public Exporter getExporter(Object obj,
                            boolean cache)
                     throws IOException,
                            ConfigurationException
The Exporter for this application using its package and name. The value returned is cached based on the value passed in cache.

The getDefaultWireProtocol() method is called to establish which default exporter to provide if none is specified in the configuration. For "JERI", the default is 

                        new BasicJeriExporter( 
                                        getDefaultServerEndpoint(),
                                        new BasicILFactory(
                                                new BasicMethodConstraints(
                                                        getJeriInvocationConstraints() ),
                                                getJeriPermissionClass()
                                        )
                                );

Configuration entry name: exporter

attachDefaultHandler

protected Handler attachDefaultHandler(Logger log)
                                throws ConfigurationException
Attach the default console handler that logs to stdout. The application can override this method to attach a different handler. This method uses a cache of attached handlers so that multiple instances of this class or any subclass will only attach the handler once. If you want different handlers for different instances, you should override this method to provide the appropriate logic.

Returns:
the handler attached to the passed logger.
Throws:
ConfigurationException
